stylometry:
Standard deviation describes how varied your data set is. The more spread out data points are the higher standard deviation the data set will have. For example: 
If you are put in a room to entertain a group of people, and told that the average age is 20 years old one might assume that the range of age would be 18-22, college students if you will. However you get there and you have people anywhere from 2 years of age to close to 40. If you would have known the standard deviation of the set you would have been able to see if the group of people you were going to be entertaining was a group of all ages, quite literally, or a group of college students. This would be essential in trying to relate, assembling jokes, tricks, etc.
